name: N-undecane
Reason: The basic unit, methane, has a melting point of -182. The addition of each methylene (CH2) group in an alkane typically raises the melting point due to increased van der Waals forces. For undecanes, which have 10 additional CH2 groups compared to methane, we would estimate an increase of approximately 2.5 degrees Celsius per CH2 group.
